race.comment: AVERRED (1) has been racing in stronger metro and provincial company and was beaten a long neck over 1666m at Ipswich last time. Maps well, and the extra metres shouldn't bother. Well placed to break through. TWILIGHT STEPS (3) is a danger. Gets out over more ground today off a quinella placing over 1400m at Sunshine Coast. Gives every indication the 1900m will suit, and he has a low barrier and a handy 2kg claim. He's suited as well. RUBOS (2) surprised the market and turned the form around, beaten 1L over 1800m at the Sunshine Coast. Enjoyed the step-up and holding the form can get into the money. PHYLISS (8) needs to lift her game considerably but may be the best of the remainder.
